<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76875" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-745x497.jpg" alt="MV Agusta Superveloce 98 Edizione Limitata" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
<span class="lede">At the ripe</span> age of 78, MV Agusta is the third-oldest Italian motorcycle company still in operation. But the company&#8217;s first motorcycle engine is even older—it was built in 1943, two years before the Meccanica Verghera Agusta brand was officially registered. Now the Varese-based marque is celebrating its birth with the release of the luxurious MV Agusta Superveloce 98 Edizione Limitata.</p>
<p>The Superveloce is the closest thing that <a href="https://www.bikeexif.com/tag/mv-agusta" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MV Agusta</a> has to a modern classic in their current range. Based on the MV Agusta F3 superbike, it uses the donor bike&#8217;s 798 cc triple-cylinder engine, steel trellis frame, aluminum swingarm, and most of its running gear. But it trades the F3&#8217;s ultra-modern fairings for more elegant bodywork, echoing the rounder aesthetics of MV Agusta&#8217;s 1970s race bikes.<span id="more-76858"></span></p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76862" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-1-745x497.jpg" alt="MV Agusta Superveloce 98 Edizione Limitata" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-1-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-1-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-1-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-1-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-1-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-1-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-1-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-1-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-1-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-1-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-1-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-1.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
First revealed in 2018, the Superveloce has come out in various versions and special edition trims since. Taking up residence alongside the current &#8216;base&#8217; model Superveloce and the swankier Superveloce S, the Superveloce 98 pays tribute to the company&#8217;s first motorcycle—the MV 98.</p>
<p>If you&#8217;re not au fait with MV Agusta&#8217;s history, we&#8217;ll bring you up to speed. The marque traces its originals back to the early 20s, which is when Giovanni Agusta co-founded the Costruzioni Aeronautiche Giovanni Agusta S.A. aircraft company. When he passed away just a few years later at the age of 48, the company was left to his wife and sons.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76878" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-14-745x497.jpg" alt="MV Agusta MV 98 engine" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-14-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-14-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-14-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-14-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-14-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-14-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-14-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-14-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-14-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-14-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-14-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-14-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-14.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
Business was good&#8230; and then the Second World War happened. A post-war ban on Italian aircraft manufacturing would have crippled the family, if not for the fact that Giovanni&#8217;s son, Domenico Agusta, had already had the idea to start building motorcycles a few years prior. He rationalized that diversifying the company would be the best way to ensure its longevity and that Italy would need affordable transport solutions after the war.</p>
<p>By 1943, the company had built its first motorcycle engine—a 98 cc single-cylinder two-stroke mill with a two-speed transmission. It went into production for all of a few weeks, before the occupation of the factory in 1943 put Domenico&#8217;s plans on pause. Two years later, the MV Agusta company was finally established—and its first motorcycle, the MV 98, was on the market.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone wp-image-76882 size-large" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-15-745x497.jpg" alt="MV Agusta Superveloce 98 Edizione Limitata" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-15-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-15-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-15-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-15-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-15-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-15-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-15-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-15-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-15-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-15-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-15-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-15-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-15.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
You could write volumes about the MV 98 alone. It was an elegant little 70 kg [154 lbs] machine, sporting 19” wheels, a girder front end, and plunger rear suspension. Its diminutive engine displayed a mechanical simplicity that is seldom seen on modern bikes.</p>
<p>But a big talking point was its color. Save for a splash of chrome on the fuel tank, most of the bike was painted in a rich burgundy hue.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76869" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-8-745x497.jpg" alt="MV Agusta Superveloce 98 Edizione Limitata" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-8-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-8-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-8-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-8-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-8-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-8-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-8-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-8-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-8-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-8-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-8-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-8-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-8.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
There aren&#8217;t many similarities between a 98 cc classic that tops out at 65 km/h [40 mph], and a modern superbike that makes 147 hp. So MV Agusta is tying the Superveloce 98 to its namesake by way of an exotic paint job and a smattering of tribute graphics.</p>
<p>The MV Agusta Superveloce 98&#8217;s metallic burgundy color is called &#8216;Rosso Verghera,&#8217; and it&#8217;s applied by hand using multiple matte layers with a gloss finish laid over them. Silver stripes run down each side of the fairing, with special &#8217;98 Edizione Limitata&#8217; logos adorning the tail section. The Superveloce&#8217;s frame and stunning cross-spoked aluminum wheels are done in silver to contrast the dark burgundy hue.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76871" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-10-745x497.jpg" alt="MV Agusta Superveloce 98 Edizione Limitata" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-10-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-10-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-10-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-10-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-10-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-10-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-10-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-10-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-10-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-10-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-10-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-10-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-10.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
Under the livery, the Superveloce 98 is pretty much identical to the Superveloce S. Its triple-cylinder engine boasts a counter-rotating crankshaft, DLC-coated cams, and a handful of titanium internals. It wears Pirelli Diablo Rosso IV Corsa tires, twin Brembo Stylema front brake calipers, and a TFT display with myriad electronic rider aids. It also weighs just 173 kilos [381 lbs] dry.</p>
<p>There&#8217;s an optional racing kit for the MV Agusta Superveloce 98 too. It includes a matching pillion seat cover, a bike cover, a racing ECU, and a blacked-out triple-exit Arrow exhaust.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76867" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-6-745x497.jpg" alt="MV Agusta Superveloce 98 Edizione Limitata" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-6-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-6-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-6-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-6-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-6-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-6-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-6-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-6-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-6-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-6-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-6-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/mv-agusta-superveloce-98-6.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
MV Agusta hasn&#8217;t announced pricing for the Superveloce 98 yet. But considering that Italian pricing for the Superveloce and Superveloce S starts at €23,100 and €27,900 respectively [$24,598 and $27,998 in the US], you can imagine.</p>
<p>You&#8217;ll need to jump quickly if you want one too. MV Agusta is only producing 300 units, each bearing a numbered laser-engraved plaque—and they claim that most of them are already spoken for by enthusiastic MV Agusta collectors.</p>
<p>Source: <a href="https://www.mvagusta.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MV Agusta</a></p>
